       your certificate

   Obtaining the Air Quality Certificate
   The Air Quality Certificate is a secure document issued on the basis of
   information which appears on the vehicle registration certificate . It
   certifies the vehicle's environmental class based on pollutant
   emissions.
   For shipments to France, its cost is 3.62€.
   The Air Quality Certificate will be sent to the delivery address you
   indicate.
   (BUTTON) Applying for your certificate
   [bandeau_accueil.png]

   Crit'Air: The Air Quality Certificate, an act of good citizenship to
   promote cleaner vehicles.
   (BUTTON) Watch the video
   [pixel_transparent.png]

All about the Air Quality Certificate

   What is the certificate?
   The certificate is a round sticker which corresponds to a vehicle class
   defined according to air pollutant emissions.
   Is it mandatory?
   The certificate is only mandatory in certain areas. It can also
   provides you with certain benefits set up by local authorities.

   Link to Ministry website
   [pixel_transparent.png]

News

   You are on the official site for the issuing of air quality
   certificates in accordance with the Order of 29 June 2016 concerning
   the procedures for the issuing and affixing of air quality
   certificates.
   Please be aware of scams : some sites offer air quality certificates at
   a higher rate than the one set by the regulations (as a reminder, it
   costs €3.11 plus postage).

   View the Order
